#check for missing values 
def missing_check(df):
    total = df.isnull().sum().sort_values(ascending=False)   # total number of null values
    percent = (df.isnull().sum()/df.isnull().count()).sort_values(ascending=False)  # percentage of values that are null
    missing_data = pd.concat([total, percent], axis=1, keys=['Total', 'Percent'])  # putting the above two together
    return missing_data # return the dataframe
missing_check(data)

# Print the predictive regression equation
print('Predictive regression equation:')
print(f'y = {float(intercept):.2f}', end=' ')
for i, coef in enumerate(coefficients[0]):
    if i == 0:
        continue
    variable_name = X_train.columns[i-0]
    print(f'+ ({coef:.2f})*{variable_name}', end=' ')

y = 49.89 + (0.06)*ZN + (0.05)*INDUS + (2.52)*CHAS + (-22.25)*NOX + (2.70)*RM + (0.00)*AGE + (-1.53)*DIS + (0.30)*RAD + (-0.01)*TAX + (-0.99)*PTRATIO + (-0.59)*LSTAT
